components.name: Download Agency Weather Data
components.description: Retrieves raw weather station CSV files from agency FTP or HTTPS endpoints.

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; starts the pipeline.

components.name: Normalize Agency Weather Data
components.description: Converts raw agency CSV data to a standard format with ISO timestamps, Celsius temperatures, and meters elevation.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful download of the same agency's raw CSV.

connections.purpose: Read raw CSV and write normalized CSV files

components.name: Merge Climate Datasets
components.description: Combines normalized datasets from all agencies into a unified climate dataset in Parquet format.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after all agency normalization tasks have succeeded.

connections.purpose: Read normalized CSV files and write the final Parquet dataset

description.description: Comprehensive climate data fusion workflow that downloads, normalizes, and merges weather station data from five meteorological agencies.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

sources: NOAA weather station CSV file from ftp://noaa.gov/weather/stations.csv
ECMWF weather station CSV file from https://ecmwf.int/data/stations.csv
JMA weather station CSV file from https://jma.go.jp/weather/stations.csv
MetOffice weather station CSV file from https://metoffice.gov.uk/data/stations.csv
BOM weather station CSV file from https://bom.gov.au/observations/stations.csv
sinks: Unified climate dataset in Parquet format stored on local filesystem (/data/unified_climate_dataset.parquet)
